"Abstract Under Article 29 of the EU Data Protection Directive, a working party has been set up which advises in relation to data protection matters. Specifically, it has been looking at the dialogue taking place between the European Commission and the US Government regarding a solution to the concern that the US does not, currently, provide adequate protection for personal data (in which event it becomes more complicated to transfer data to the US). This article explores the basis of the controversy and the likelihood that the current negotiations will find a workable solution."
